WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.406 --> 00:00:06.440
[Rip]
<i>This'll be one of those days</i>

2
00:00:06.574 --> 00:00:08.109
that follow you to the grave.

3
00:00:08.209 --> 00:00:09.577
If either one of you
want to walk.

4
00:00:09.677 --> 00:00:11.212
- I won't hold it against you.
- We're with you.

5
00:00:11.312 --> 00:00:13.481
♪ dramatic. suspenseful music ♪

6
00:00:14.415 --> 00:00:16.417
- [Beth] How does this happen?
- [Rip] Foot-and-mouth.

7
00:00:16.517 --> 00:00:17.651
It's got to be the new bull.

8
00:00:17.751 --> 00:00:19.787
Cattle broker.
he fucked us. baby.

9
00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:22.623
<i>All the vet paperwork? Forged.</i>

10
00:00:24.792 --> 00:00:25.926
[bellowing]

11
00:00:26.027 --> 00:00:27.428
<i>I don't know how
we're gonna tell Carter.</i>

12
00:00:27.561 --> 00:00:29.897
You're the prettiest woman
I've ever seen.

13
00:00:29.998 --> 00:00:31.598
Carter has a pure heart.

14
00:00:31.599 --> 00:00:32.800
If you fuck with it.

15
00:00:32.933 --> 00:00:34.435
I will make your life
a living hell.

16
00:00:34.568 --> 00:00:36.437
- What's your day rate. chief?
- Whatever you're paying.

17
00:00:36.537 --> 00:00:38.806
Let's scoot.
[yells]

18
00:00:38.906 --> 00:00:39.974
- [growls]
- I named her Xena.

19
00:00:40.074 --> 00:00:42.776
after the Warrior Princess.

20
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:44.978
Someone at the 10-Petal

21
00:00:44.979 --> 00:00:46.446
<i>knows more than they're saying.</i>

22
00:00:46.447 --> 00:00:48.116
[Wade] <i>That's a pretty
serious accusation.</i>

23
00:00:48.249 --> 00:00:49.782
[Whitney] <i>Yeah. well.
so is disappearing a man.</i>

24
00:00:49.783 --> 00:00:51.319
Let me take over.
Let me do the job for you.

25
00:00:51.452 --> 00:00:54.955
I wish I could. Kino.
Wish I could.

26
00:00:56.090 --> 00:00:58.292
- You sold me a sick bull.
- [yelling]

27
00:00:58.426 --> 00:01:00.327
You got 30 seconds to get
the fuck out of Rio Paloma.

28
00:01:00.328 --> 00:01:03.564
<i>and if I ever fucking see
your face again. you're dead.</i>

29
00:01:07.568 --> 00:01:10.471
♪ slow. somber music ♪

30
00:01:21.482 --> 00:01:23.717
[Rip]
Sure is quiet. isn't it?

31
00:01:24.785 --> 00:01:27.688
It ain't a ranch
without a herd. sweetheart.

32
00:01:29.823 --> 00:01:32.926
We'll fill these pastures
again one day.

33
00:01:33.694 --> 00:01:36.597
Might just take us a minute.
that's all.

34
00:01:38.466 --> 00:01:39.833
Yeah.

35
00:01:44.338 --> 00:01:47.275
Carter still hasn't
spoken to me.

36
00:01:48.942 --> 00:01:51.011
I should have told him.

37
00:01:52.513 --> 00:01:55.583
You ought to just give him
some time. He'll come around.

38
00:01:58.686 --> 00:02:00.088
You sure about this?

39
00:02:02.022 --> 00:02:05.393
Honey. it'll pay the bills
and put food on the table.

40
00:02:07.295 --> 00:02:08.929
Till we come up with a plan.

41
00:02:10.664 --> 00:02:12.700
We'll come up with a plan.

42
00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:18.038
- I love you.
- Love you.

43
00:02:29.717 --> 00:02:31.385
All right.

44
00:02:32.553 --> 00:02:35.556
♪

45
00:02:45.366 --> 00:02:46.700
<i>♪ Step right up ♪</i>

46
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:48.136
["The Grand Tour"
by George Jones playing]

47
00:02:48.236 --> 00:02:50.938
[singing along]
<i>♪ Come on in ♪</i>

48
00:02:51.038 --> 00:02:52.940
<i>♪ If you'd like ♪</i>

49
00:02:53.073 --> 00:02:56.244
<i>♪ To take the grand tour ♪</i>

50
00:02:56.344 --> 00:02:59.612
<i>♪ Of a lonely house ♪</i>

51
00:02:59.613 --> 00:03:04.084
<i>♪ That once was
home sweet home... ♪</i>

52
00:03:04.852 --> 00:03:06.919
That's Beulah's son Joaquin.

53
00:03:06.920 --> 00:03:10.924
None of them are easy.
but he's reasonable.

54
00:03:11.058 --> 00:03:13.427
[panting]

55
00:03:15.729 --> 00:03:18.466
Morning. Joaquin.

56
00:03:18.599 --> 00:03:20.268
This is Rip Wheeler.

57
00:03:20.368 --> 00:03:22.603
Beulah wants to meet him.

58
00:03:22.736 --> 00:03:24.071
She expecting you?

59
00:03:24.172 --> 00:03:25.473
We didn't fix a time.

60
00:03:25.606 --> 00:03:27.941
but I ain't ever caught
your mother off guard.

61
00:03:28.709 --> 00:03:31.512
Huh. Come on in.

62
00:03:34.848 --> 00:03:37.818
[Everett]
Never ceases to amaze. the...

63
00:03:37.951 --> 00:03:40.954
the shit wealthy waste
their wealth on.

64
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.623
Yeah.

65
00:03:43.424 --> 00:03:45.793
She wants to speak
with you. Alone.

66
00:03:45.926 --> 00:03:47.127
Okay.

67
00:03:47.228 --> 00:03:48.829
Godspeed.
I'll wait for you in the truck.

68
00:03:55.636 --> 00:03:57.638
[exhales heavily]

69
00:04:01.742 --> 00:04:05.346
[sighs] I don't normally
take meetings at this hour.

70
00:04:05.446 --> 00:04:08.782
Well. Everett mentioned that
I might be able to help you.

71
00:04:08.882 --> 00:04:10.651
Oh.

72
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:16.290
Uh. I hear you managed
the Yellowstone.

73
00:04:16.390 --> 00:04:18.158
Yes. ma'am. 25 years.

74
00:04:18.259 --> 00:04:19.460
Uh-huh. Then you bought

75
00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:21.362
the Edwards Ranch
with the Dutton girl?

76
00:04:21.462 --> 00:04:23.496
- My wife Beth. Yeah.
- Ah.

77
00:04:23.497 --> 00:04:25.164
It's good land.
it's better cattle.

78
00:04:25.165 --> 00:04:27.635
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

79
00:04:31.004 --> 00:04:33.507
You ever foreman'd
two properties?

80
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:35.509
All due respect. ma'am.
your ranch

81
00:04:35.609 --> 00:04:37.010
and my ranch put together

82
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:39.680
ain't a quarter
of what the Yellowstone is.

83
00:04:39.780 --> 00:04:41.014
So. you're a man
with an appetite.

84
00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:43.551
Nah. I'm just a man
that likes to work.

85
00:04:43.651 --> 00:04:45.386
Well. that's
an attractive quality.

86
00:04:45.519 --> 00:04:46.820
[chuckles]

87
00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:50.190
If you don't mind me asking.
who is. uh. Rob-Will?

88
00:04:50.291 --> 00:04:52.859
My son. Y'all have met?

89
00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:54.362
Briefly. yeah. Yeah.

90
00:04:54.462 --> 00:04:57.730
Well. let's just say
he's on an indefinite vacation.

91
00:04:57.731 --> 00:04:59.400
What else did Everett tell you?

92
00:04:59.533 --> 00:05:03.036
- Which part?
- About me needing help.

93
00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:04.338
Oh. uh...

94
00:05:04.438 --> 00:05:06.072
He mentioned that
your current foreman--

95
00:05:06.073 --> 00:05:08.709
these are his words. of course--
"is a fucking idiot."

96
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.778
[laughs]

97
00:05:10.878 --> 00:05:13.913
Ah. McKinney. He doesn't
pull punches. does he?

98
00:05:13.914 --> 00:05:15.916
No. ma'am. he doesn't.

99
00:05:17.551 --> 00:05:19.587
[sighs]
Well...

100
00:05:21.355 --> 00:05:22.923
...we got 75.000 acres.

101
00:05:23.023 --> 00:05:27.261
about 2.200 head.
Mexican crossbreed.

102
00:05:27.395 --> 00:05:29.929
We sell to big-box retailers.
but...

103
00:05:29.930 --> 00:05:32.633
mismanagement has been
a bit of a bugaboo of late.

104
00:05:32.733 --> 00:05:35.569
Well. would you like me
to fix your problem?

105
00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:36.904
Well. I wonder. can you?

106
00:05:37.037 --> 00:05:38.238
If it's ranching. I can.
Yes. ma'am.

107
00:05:38.372 --> 00:05:40.940
My margins have grown
razor-thin.

108
00:05:40.941 --> 00:05:44.243
I need someone
who implements efficiency.

109
00:05:44.244 --> 00:05:46.447
A man who works smarter.
not just harder.

110
00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:49.082
Well. I can do both.

111
00:05:49.182 --> 00:05:51.419
I like a tight-lipped ship.

112
00:05:51.552 --> 00:05:53.754
Rio Paloma loves to gossip.

113
00:05:53.854 --> 00:05:57.991
Well. ma'am. other people's
business. it ain't mine.

114
00:06:00.428 --> 00:06:03.130
Well. few names are
as revered as John Dutton's.

115
00:06:03.263 --> 00:06:06.132
I suppose if you worked
for him for 25 years.

116
00:06:06.133 --> 00:06:08.436
- you can work for anyone.
- Hmm.

117
00:06:10.203 --> 00:06:13.474
I also know that.
despite its tragic end.

118
00:06:13.574 --> 00:06:15.776
the Yellowstone was not
a three-ring circus.

119
00:06:15.876 --> 00:06:17.244
♪ slow. somber music ♪

120
00:06:17.345 --> 00:06:19.680
No. I wouldn't allow it.

121
00:06:20.748 --> 00:06:22.450
Do whatever it takes
to get my ranch in order.

122
00:06:22.550 --> 00:06:24.117
and I'll pay you handsomely.

123
00:06:24.251 --> 00:06:27.788
not just with my money
but with my loyalty.

124
00:06:27.888 --> 00:06:29.657
Hmm.

125
00:06:30.924 --> 00:06:33.961
I'll be here at 4:30 a.m.

126
00:06:34.061 --> 00:06:35.663
Pleasure to meet you.
Ms. Jackson.

127
00:06:35.963 --> 00:06:37.865
♪

128
00:06:38.666 --> 00:06:40.868
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

129
00:07:02.990 --> 00:07:06.159
♪

130
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:32.285
♪

131
00:07:46.934 --> 00:07:49.202
- [wood creaks]
- [Rip sighs]

132
00:07:50.571 --> 00:07:53.206
You know this isn't
our only option.

133
00:07:54.007 --> 00:07:55.776
I could make some calls.

134
00:07:56.577 --> 00:07:58.278
Dallas. New York.

135
00:07:58.412 --> 00:08:00.848
I could be earning
within a month.

136
00:08:01.682 --> 00:08:04.151
But I'd be gone.

137
00:08:05.018 --> 00:08:07.154
No.

138
00:08:08.589 --> 00:08:10.691
I don't want that. darling.

139
00:08:12.360 --> 00:08:14.395
I want you next to me.

140
00:08:15.128 --> 00:08:17.130
Well. I'm always next to you.

141
00:08:17.264 --> 00:08:19.666
♪ gentle music ♪

142
00:08:19.667 --> 00:08:21.435
I'll see you in a bit. sweetie.

143
00:08:35.315 --> 00:08:37.518
♪

144
00:08:57.270 --> 00:08:59.640
♪

145
00:09:16.524 --> 00:09:19.393
♪ dramatic. soaring music ♪

146
00:09:41.381 --> 00:09:43.551
♪

147
00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:03.303
♪

148
00:10:21.421 --> 00:10:23.591
♪

149
00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:30.330
[TV playing indistinctly]

150
00:10:35.035 --> 00:10:36.470
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

151
00:10:36.604 --> 00:10:38.606
["Ain't That Right"
by Charley Crockett playing]

152
00:10:38.706 --> 00:10:41.108
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

153
00:10:41.909 --> 00:10:44.177
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

154
00:10:46.146 --> 00:10:48.448
<i>♪ We were up above it all ♪</i>

155
00:10:48.549 --> 00:10:51.451
<i>♪ Flying in your plane ♪</i>

156
00:10:51.585 --> 00:10:54.922
<i>♪ About the time
I had a bloody Mary ♪</i>

157
00:10:55.022 --> 00:10:58.458
<i>♪ Lord. I wasn't
feeling anything ♪</i>

158
00:10:58.592 --> 00:11:00.794
<i>♪ There you was
in all that leather ♪</i>

159
00:11:00.894 --> 00:11:04.131
<i>♪ With something on your mind ♪</i>

160
00:11:04.231 --> 00:11:07.333
<i>♪ I found out just what it was ♪</i>

161
00:11:07.334 --> 00:11:09.970
<i>♪ In the Salt Lake City lights ♪</i>

162
00:11:10.070 --> 00:11:12.439
- <i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>
- [coffee pouring]

163
00:11:12.540 --> 00:11:13.473
Who is that?

164
00:11:13.607 --> 00:11:15.142
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

165
00:11:15.275 --> 00:11:16.309
Yeah. who the fuck are you?

166
00:11:16.443 --> 00:11:18.779
<i>♪ Ain't that right... ♪</i>

167
00:11:18.879 --> 00:11:20.948
We got calves to wean.

168
00:11:22.716 --> 00:11:24.851
Get your gear together

169
00:11:24.852 --> 00:11:27.387
and get your asses
in the saddle.

170
00:11:28.488 --> 00:11:31.158
Y'all got ten minutes.

171
00:11:33.093 --> 00:11:34.662
[music stops]

172
00:11:35.529 --> 00:11:38.031
Wait. I know you.
From the gas station.

173
00:11:38.131 --> 00:11:40.333
♪ exciting music ♪

174
00:11:48.709 --> 00:11:51.011
This is fucking bullshit.

175
00:12:01.789 --> 00:12:04.057
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

176
00:12:10.197 --> 00:12:11.832
- [Zach] Ma'am?
- Yeah?

177
00:12:11.932 --> 00:12:14.034
Horses are cared for.

178
00:12:14.134 --> 00:12:15.402
Anything else I can do?

179
00:12:15.535 --> 00:12:18.772
You can stop calling me "ma'am."

180
00:12:19.539 --> 00:12:21.909
- I've got a name.
- Oh. okay.

181
00:12:22.009 --> 00:12:25.078
Just know
that no work's beneath me.

182
00:12:32.219 --> 00:12:34.554
- He'd have liked you.
- Who?

183
00:12:35.355 --> 00:12:36.790
My dad.

184
00:12:37.591 --> 00:12:40.427
Sure would've liked
to have met him.

185
00:12:51.905 --> 00:12:53.607
Want one?

186
00:12:54.507 --> 00:12:55.809
Got one.

187
00:13:03.516 --> 00:13:06.153
Not much of a ranch anymore.

188
00:13:09.589 --> 00:13:11.258
Thank you.

189
00:13:14.695 --> 00:13:16.630
I keep looking for the herd.

190
00:13:18.398 --> 00:13:20.768
You know.
like they're still here.

191
00:13:21.669 --> 00:13:24.137
Take away something
you see every day...

192
00:13:25.005 --> 00:13:28.641
...sun. birds.

193
00:13:28.642 --> 00:13:30.477
wind even...

194
00:13:32.445 --> 00:13:34.848
...brain can't quite catch up.

195
00:13:39.286 --> 00:13:41.421
Was it 15 years you were inside?

196
00:13:43.223 --> 00:13:45.058
It's a long fucking time.

197
00:13:47.394 --> 00:13:49.628
What'd you miss the most?

198
00:13:49.629 --> 00:13:51.865
Lots of things.

199
00:13:54.034 --> 00:13:57.537
But mostly. the peace and quiet
of a lonely night.

200
00:13:59.306 --> 00:14:00.974
Yeah. I'd miss that.

201
00:14:01.809 --> 00:14:05.412
Not sure I'm meant
for peace. though.

202
00:14:07.414 --> 00:14:09.449
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

203
00:14:09.549 --> 00:14:11.351
Me. neither.

204
00:14:14.187 --> 00:14:17.925
But they say
God's ways are mysterious.

205
00:14:18.792 --> 00:14:20.493
Yeah.

206
00:14:20.593 --> 00:14:22.229
Mystery's right out there.

207
00:14:23.030 --> 00:14:25.265
For me. anyway.

208
00:14:26.066 --> 00:14:27.701
Right here.

209
00:14:30.303 --> 00:14:32.773
Land's as good a God as any.

210
00:14:34.107 --> 00:14:36.076
Maybe better.

211
00:14:40.748 --> 00:14:42.916
We keep looking. then.

212
00:14:43.683 --> 00:14:46.153
Keep trying. that's for sure.

213
00:14:50.991 --> 00:14:53.827
Hey. whatever you're working on
over there. Beth...

214
00:14:56.529 --> 00:14:58.531
...I hope it works.

215
00:14:58.631 --> 00:15:00.801
It fucking better.

216
00:15:08.475 --> 00:15:10.410
♪ fast. exciting music ♪

217
00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.545
[Rip]
Go on. start turning them out.

218
00:15:12.645 --> 00:15:13.913
[cattle lowing]

219
00:15:13.914 --> 00:15:16.582
[shouting. whistling]

220
00:15:16.583 --> 00:15:18.886
- Hey!
- Hey!

221
00:15:18.986 --> 00:15:20.020
Hey!

222
00:15:20.120 --> 00:15:23.223
[shouting. whistling]

223
00:15:26.393 --> 00:15:28.595
[shouting]

224
00:15:28.728 --> 00:15:30.097
[whistles]

225
00:15:30.197 --> 00:15:32.399
Go. keep turning them back.
let's go!

226
00:15:32.499 --> 00:15:34.367
- [whistles]
- Come on. Come on!

227
00:15:34.467 --> 00:15:36.203
Out of my way.

228
00:15:45.145 --> 00:15:48.415
[indistinct shouting]

229
00:15:48.515 --> 00:15:50.450
- [whistles]
- Find the gate. [grunts]

230
00:15:50.583 --> 00:15:52.419
- Hey!
- [shushing]

231
00:15:52.519 --> 00:15:54.354
Hey.

232
00:15:58.258 --> 00:15:59.960
- [whistling]
- Fucking son of a bitch

233
00:16:00.093 --> 00:16:02.095
doesn't know what spiderweb
he just walked into.

234
00:16:02.195 --> 00:16:04.463
Man. it was past time
to wean these calves.

235
00:16:04.464 --> 00:16:05.765
Fuck. Tommy. you think

236
00:16:05.866 --> 00:16:07.234
- I didn't know that?
- Quit fucking talking

237
00:16:07.334 --> 00:16:08.768
and go get them pairs.

238
00:16:08.869 --> 00:16:10.303
[Tommy]
Ah. yes. sir.

239
00:16:10.403 --> 00:16:11.839
[whooping]

240
00:16:12.672 --> 00:16:14.441
[Chet grunts]

241
00:16:14.541 --> 00:16:16.776
Hey!

242
00:16:20.914 --> 00:16:22.449
[cattle lowing]

243
00:16:28.822 --> 00:16:30.390
[vehicle approaching]

244
00:16:52.279 --> 00:16:53.881
[truck door opens]

245
00:16:58.518 --> 00:17:00.921
♪ slow. gentle music ♪

246
00:17:02.522 --> 00:17:05.358
[metal clanking]

247
00:17:07.427 --> 00:17:09.496
[creaking]

248
00:17:09.629 --> 00:17:11.331
Thought you could use
a little pick-me-up.

249
00:17:11.464 --> 00:17:13.133
It's not too soon?

250
00:17:13.233 --> 00:17:16.703
Nah. Some days.
too soon's all we got.

251
00:17:18.471 --> 00:17:21.008
Okay. girl. There you go.

252
00:17:21.108 --> 00:17:22.509
[clicking tongue]

253
00:17:22.642 --> 00:17:25.344
- How is she?
- She's doing great.

254
00:17:25.345 --> 00:17:29.382
You know. like you said.
this girl's got spirit.

255
00:17:29.516 --> 00:17:31.351
You got it. you got it.
There you go.

256
00:17:32.252 --> 00:17:33.853
Oh.

257
00:17:33.954 --> 00:17:36.222
There you go. Good job.

